title: UAW, Fiat Chrysler Reach Tentative Labor Deal
text:
UAW, Fiat Chrysler Reach Tentative Labor Deal Union hopes agreement can serve as a template to be used in later talks with Ford, GM By jeff.bennett@wsj.com Updated Sept. 15, 2015 7:38 p.m. ET 
The United Auto Workers union and Fiat Chrysler Automobiles NV reached a tentative labor deal Tuesday following a marathon night of negotiations, hammering out a template the union hopes can be used for later talks with Detroitâ€™s other two big auto makers. 
Fiat Chrysler Chief Sergio Marchionne and UAW President Dennis Williams were to take questions from the media at a news conference scheduled to begin shortly in Detroit.
